		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In <em>Super Mario Bros. 3</em>, the mushroom houses and spade minigame show largely the same elements at different scales. The small versions have slightly less color detail (Mario's black overalls and skin-tone sclera and Toad's skin-tone cap) due to palette limits, but the only difference in elements is that the proportions on the Toad in the spade minigame look a lot younger. (Game sprite Mario's ears are F'd up as well though.)<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<span class="gensmall"><b>File comment:</b> From left to right:<br />Raccoon Mario in spade minigame<br />Raccoon Mario in game and mushroom house<br />Toad in spade minigame<br />Toad in mushroom house</span><br />
		
